 @custom:oz-upgrades-unsafe-allow constructor

@custom:function-name initialize
@param initialAdmin the initial admin and the owner of the contract
@param _vaultInfo the vault info that will be saved on the contract
@dev this is used in palce of a constructor to initialize a proxy's state using this implemetation's logic

@custom:function-name _authorizeUpgrade
@param newImplementation implementation address
@dev this is a function required by solidity and the openzeppelin UUPS contract
this is used to prevent unauthorized account to upgrade the contract

@custom:function-name reward
@param to the receiver of the reward
@param amount the amount of tokens to reward
@return success if the transaction succeeded or not
@dev this function is used to reward a single user of a specified amount of reward token

@custom:function-name rewardBatch
@param receivers an array of receivers to send rewards to
@custom:sub-param `receiver` - address of the user to reward
@custom:sub-param `amount` - amount of token to reward the user
@return returnData the result of the batch reward transaction
@dev this function is used to reward users in batches

@custom:function-name getVaultInfo
@return info the vault info of the contract
@dev this function is used to fetch the vault info of the vault

@custom:function-name rewardPool
@return pool the amount of reward tokens left for rewards
@dev this function is used to view the remaining balance of the contract for
the * currently set reward token

@custom:function-name defaultControllerLimits
@return quota the max amount of users
@return allowance the max amount of reward tokens
@dev this function is used to check the default controller limits the contract is currently using

@custom:function-name controllerLimits
@param controller the controller address
@return quota the max amount of users left
@return allowance the max amount of reward tokens left
@dev this function is used to check the remaining limits of a given controller

@custom:function-name controllerLimitsEnabled
@return enabled is controller limits enabled or not
@dev this function is used to check if the limits on the controllers is in effect or not

@custom:function-name setDefaultControllerLimits
@param quota the max amount of users the controller is allowed to reward
@param rewardAllowance the max amount of reward token the controller is allowed to distribute
@dev this function is used to set the default limits that will be used when granting controller permit

@custom:function-name setControllerLimits
@param controller the controller address
@param quota the max amount of users the controller is allowed to reward
@param rewardAllowance the max amount of reward token the controller is allowed to distribute
@dev this function is used to set the limits on specifc controllers

@custom:function-name updateRewardToken
@param newRewardToken the new reward token
@dev this function is used to change the reward token used in rewarding users

@custom:function-name withdrawToken
@param tokenAddress the token address the admin wants to withdraw
@param amount the amount of token to withdraw
@return success if the transaction succeeded
@dev this function is used to withdraw tokens from the contract
for various reasons like;
- incorrect token deposit
- unused reward token
and more

@custom:function-name changeVaultOwner
@param newOwner the new contract owner
@dev this function is used to tranfer ownership and all roles from one account to another while also
removing all permissions on the previous account

@custom:function-name _spendRewardLimits
@param controller the controller address
@param amount the amount of allowance to spend
@dev a private function used to spend controller limits on rewards

@custom:function-name grantPermit
@param controller the controller contract
@dev used to grant permision for selected (onlyRole Restricted) functions to the controller

@custom:function-name _grantPermit
@param controller the controller address
@dev a private fucntion that handles all setups when granting controller permit and is also used
diring initialization to grant the admin proper controller permissions

@custom:function-name revokePermit
@param controller the controller contract
@dev used to grant permision for selected (onlyRole Restricted) functions to the controller

@custom:function-name _revokePermit
@param controller the controller address
@dev a private fucntion that handles all setups when revoking controller permit

@custom:function-name isController
@param controller the controller address
@dev used to check if an address is a controller or has a controller access

